onbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=463.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High school student needing help with future here....</span><hr size=1> Hey falcon...I've been seeing a lot of you...<br>
I just got done an exchange like that...my school and a school in japan have kind of a deal going...It's a really relaxed exchange and it's only for a month (in the summer)...so it's not quite the commitment it takes for a full year...the only catch was you had to pay for the plane ticket which was $1500...The student came back here and we had a great time...I had ridiculously good time there...words can't describe it...If you do go...don't say no to anything...sure you'll eventually hit some things you don't like but you don't want to miss out on something you may love...If you look around there are some adult exchanges...the same teacher that does the exchange at our school does an adult exchange...it's about $5000 but that's all inclusive...you should be able to find something...as well you could make friends with someone there and stay there and go on vacation...or do what I plan on doing after post secondary...Teach english...it's a good way to see Japan for a few years and get payed to do it... <p>--
Power corrupts but absolute power is kinda neat 
---               
Single Handedly saving the porn industry
--
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufalcondelta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FalconDelta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/17/01 4:22:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=463.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hipolymer.virtualave.net/images/Delta.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High school student needing help with future here....</span><hr size=1> WOW... so cool you've been there, that's awesome. You have to tell me more about it. I am so excited about going there this summer. I went down to the local university in my area and checked out some books on japanese language just to get a jump start. It's a tough language to learn, but i figure once i am in college i can get help there. What sort of places did you go to while you were there? I hear karaoke is a big thing there. My grandparents went there a few years back and they said that they had a grand time. Are there any places that are really worth making the effort to see while there?<br>
<br>
-Falcon<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/17/01 9:22:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=463.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High school student needing help with future here....</span><hr size=1> Well...this is really changing the subject.....<br>
I was in the tottori prefecture (about the same as a state or province)...<br>
it's on the korean side about 3hours west of osaka...<br>
what you should do is go to the old area and see the stuff in Kyoto and Nara...especially this massive buddah...ask any japanese they'll no what you mean...it's a buddah that's about 6 storeys tall and you might see pictures but nothing makes sense untill you're there....there's also a big building made of gold<br>
also go up the mountains...there's roads up most of them but they're hard to find...Try going up the mountains at night so you can see the lights...bring a flashlight though...I didn't and had to climb down without one<br>
and if you're in the tottori prefecture...try and go to the daisen fire festival...I didn't get to go but it's supposed to be sweet...<br>
If you like cars and know what you're looking for in the stats go to a car dealership and get some brochures...they're free and you can learn katakana and some kanji...as well autotrader style magazines help too... <p>--
