</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufalcondelta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FalconDelta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/18/01 5:29:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=463.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hipolymer.virtualave.net/images/Delta.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High school student needing help with future here....</span><hr size=1> Sounds like there is a whole bunch to do there. Hopefully the exchange program wont restric my movements too much. My friend went to this one Zen temple place on a mountain or hill or something and they said it was really cool. I forget the name so I have to talk in generalities. (zen temple on mountain top = very vague) but oh well... I was trying to do some research and get a collection of places that I wanted to go. I wanted to pick up some swords over there too and a couple of other martial arts things. I just hope with all the crazy terrorism stuff I'll be able to ship them back through customs. Now that hell registration week is over at my school, I will actually have time to go in and talk to the people that run the exchange program and find out more about it.<br>
<br>
-Falcon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/18/01 7:49:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=463.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High school student needing help with future here....</span><hr size=1> Hmmm...bringing swords across the border...I think if it can be considered a weapon you're @#%$ out of luck...maybe a practice sword made from bamboo...or possibly a decorative sword...doubtfull...you'd have to pay duty too because it'd be well over $500 there's no way around that...you'd be better off to mail it and get it when you get home...I think if you can hijack a plane with boxcutters a samurai sword and some nunchucks would draw attention...<br>
you can get nice stuff over here...but I know it's not the same...I'm sure you can do it but it likely won't be easy...or cheap...and you can't hide it in an x-ray machine either <p>--
Power corrupts but absolute power is kinda neat 
