</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utairomu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tairomu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/24/01 7:05:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=463.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: High school student needing help with future here....</span><hr size=1> I think the swords are going to be a negative since in japan they dont have guns they are banned so it will be even harder for you to get them and even more to get them through customs.  You can get them imported would probably be a better idea and it will save you less hassle during your trip too.  You can find good programs through various schools but right now I would take the one that would be the most inexpensive as well as being able to see all things you want to see in japan.  Where do you want to go? Tokyo, Osaka, Okinawa......  You should think about that too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#336699>- </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs>Polykarbon BBS</a><font color=#336699> - </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5>Japanese Language Help</a> <font color=#336699> - </font><a href="http://www.polykarbon.com">Polykarbon: Manga & Photoshop</a><font color=#336699> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  